---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Runtime">
  <h1>Runtime</h1>

  <p>Handles agent execution in isolated subprocesses. Two implementations: <code>Executor</code> for single agents, <code>NestedExecutor</code> for multi-agent call graphs.</p>

  <h2>Executor</h2>
  <p>Executes a single agent against an input via <code>bun:eval</code>.</p>

  <pre><code>import &lcub; Executor &rcub; from "agent-forge/runtime/executor";

const executor = new Executor();

const result = await executor.execute(agentCode, &lcub;
  pr_url: "https://github.com/org/repo/pull/123",
  repo: "org/repo",
&rcub;);

// result.output: unknown
// result.error: string or undefined
// result.executionTimeMs: number
// result.stdout: string
// result.stderr: string</code></pre>

  <h3>Execution Flow</h3>
  <pre><code>1. Create temp files:
   /tmp/agent-forge-runtime/agent_runId.ts
   /tmp/agent-forge-runtime/runtime_runId.ts
   /tmp/agent-forge-runtime/input_runId.json

2. Write agent code + runtime shim + input

3. Spawn: bun run agent_runId.ts

4. Capture stdout/stderr

5. Parse JSON output

6. Clean up temp files</code></pre>

  <h3>Runtime Shim</h3>
  <p>Every agent execution injects a runtime package providing tool implementations:</p>
  <pre><code>export const tools = &lcub;
  read_file: async (&lcub; path &rcub;) returns object,
  run_command: async (&lcub; cmd, cwd &rcub;) returns object,
  gh_api: async (&lcub; endpoint, method &rcub;) returns object,
  grep: async (&lcub; pattern, path &rcub;) returns array,
  write_file: async (&lcub; path, content &rcub;) returns void,
  search_web: async (&lcub; query &rcub;) returns string,
&rcub;;</code></pre>

  <h2>NestedExecutor</h2>
  <p>Extends Executor with multi-agent support. Agents can call sub-agents via <code>call_agent(name, input)</code>.</p>

  <pre><code>import &lcub; NestedExecutor &rcub; from "agent-forge/runtime/nested_executor";

const nested = new NestedExecutor();

const result = await nested.executeTopLevel("orchestrator_agent", &lcub;
  task: "analyze this PR",
&rcub;);

// result.output: unknown
// result.callGraph: string[]  // agents in the call chain
// result.depthLimitReached: boolean or undefined
// result.cycleDetected: boolean or undefined</code></pre>

  <h3>Depth Limit</h3>
  <pre><code>// Default: MAX_DEPTH = 3
// Configurable via AGENT_MAX_DEPTH env var

Depth 0: User calls agent A
Depth 1: A calls agent B
Depth 2: B calls agent C
Depth 3: C calls agent D - REJECTED (depth exceeded)</code></pre>

  <h3>Cycle Detection</h3>
  <p>The call stack is maintained per execution. If an agent at depth N calls an agent that is already in the stack at depth N, it's rejected as a cycle:</p>
  <pre><code>// A calls B (depth 1)
// B calls C (depth 2)
// C calls A (depth 3) - REJECTED: A already in stack at depth 0</code></pre>

  <h2>Tool Registration</h2>
  <p>To enable <code>call_agent</code> within an agent's runtime:</p>
  <pre><code>const callAgentTool = NestedExecutor.registerCallAgentTool(nested);
// callAgentTool(&lcub; agent: "sub_agent_name", params: &lcub; ... &rcub; &rcub;)</code></pre>
  <p>This would be wired into the runtime shim when executing nested agents, allowing agents to invoke each other as tools.</p>

  <h2>Timeout</h2>
  <p>Default execution timeout is 30 seconds per agent. Set via constructor or <code>AGENT_TIMEOUT_MS</code> env var.</p>
</Layout>
